cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper deals with deep neural networks and their ability to generalize across changes in input distributions, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper proposes an unsupervised domain adaptation method that aligns correlations of layer activations in deep neural networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
